data.text:
The Disco Boys are a German DJ duo, based in Hamburg. Their type of music is called "disco house" but sometimes it goes as "french house". The Disco Boys consist of Raphael Krickow and Gordon Hollenga.

Their incomparable mixture of disco classics and old samples with today's modern house, gave them a large fan base in the early century, far beyond the borders of Hamburg. They are performing frequently as DJs on clubs all over the world, but mostly in Germany.

Here is an example of The Disco Boys and their video For You:http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F6DYUq-GWhQ—Singles and albumsTheir most known singles are:* I Love You So* For You* Here On My Own* B-B-B Baby* What You WantThey've published 7 albums up to this date (2007-06-16).

They each consist of two CDs with over two hours of mixed tracks, all into one big mix. The albums are:* The Disco Boys Vol.1 (2001)* The Disco Boys Vol.2 (2002)* The Disco Boys Vol.3 (2003)* The Disco Boys Vol.

4 (2004)* The Disco Boys Vol.5 (2005)* The Disco Boys Vol.6 (2006)* The Disco Boys Vol.7 (2007)* The Disco Boys Vol.8 (2007)—More onlineTheir official webpage is: http://www.discoboys.de/ (all german).

And their MySpace page is: http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&friendID=101893037
